<chapter>
	<title>Gentoo News</title>
<section>
<title>SELinux i686 LiveCD now available</title>
<body>
<p>
Much progress has been made recently in integrating <uri link="http://www.nsa.gov/selinux/">SELinux</uri> into Gentoo Linux, and now we're proud to announce that an experimental SELinux i686 <uri link="http://gentoo.oregonstate.edu/experimental/x86/livecd/">LiveCD</uri> is available, along with fresh <uri link="http://gentoo.oregonstate.edu/experimental/x86/stages/">stages</uri> 1 through 3.  The <uri link="http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/hardened/selinux/selinux-x86-install.xml">install guide</uri> is also experimental, but now users should be able to install SELinux from scratch.  Tread with care, and make sure to <uri link="http://bugs.gentoo.org/">report bugs</uri>.  The only current known issue has to do with denials from DHCP when booting from the LiveCD.
</p>
<p>For more SELinux-related info (baselayout has been modified to make /sbin/init the initial policy load), read <uri link="http://article.gmane.org/gmane.linux.gentoo.devel/15361">Chris PeBenito</uri>'s message to gentoo-dev.
</p>
</body>
</section>
</chapter>
